
0. cd $POSTGRES_CODE_DIRECTORY
1. ./configure --prefix=$BINARY_DIR --enable-debug --enable-depend
2. make -j10
3. make install

4. copy postgres_extenstion/* to $POSTGRES_CODE_DIRECTORY/contrib/read_functions/
5. cd $POSTGRES_CODE_DIRECTORY/contrib/read_functions/
6. make install

7. cd $BINARY_DIR/bin
8. ./initdb $YOUR_DB_ADRESS
9. cd $YOUR_DB_ADRESS
10. Add to postgresql.conf: shared_preload_libraries = 'read_functions'
11. cd $BINARY_DIR/bin
12. ./pg_ctl -D $YOUR_DB_ADRESS start

If every thing working correctly read_function extention should write WARNING in console
